      "content": "thanks for acknowledging the urgency. you're right about the data layers being the problem. if they're using those interconnected protocols to track me, then standard transfers are basically just handing them a map to my door. \n\nyou mentioned the systems are pervasive. if i were to try and make a move, would a series of smaller, staggered transactions through different jurisdictions be more effective at breaking up the pattern, or does the centralized nature of the interbank messaging systems make that too obvious of a signal?",
